# EDXcellence CRM ‚Äî Full-Stack Role-Based Admin Panel  
A production-ready CRM system built with **React + Vite + Tailwind**, **NodeJS + Express**, and **MongoDB** featuring complete **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)**.  
Designed for high-performance EdTech workflows: student lead management, deal tracking, user administration, analytics, and team operations.

---

## üöÄ Features

### üîê Authentication & Security
- JWT authentication (access + refresh ready)
- Protected routes with `AuthGuard`
- Fully implemented **Role-Based Access Control**
- Four default roles:
  - `SuperAdmin`
  - `Admin`
  - `Manager`
  - `Staff`
- Permission matrix enforced on both backend + frontend
- Activity logs for all admin actions

### üìä Dashboard & Analytics
- Lead analytics (daily, weekly)
- Revenue overview
- User growth metrics
- Chart.js-powered graphs
- EDXcellence-branded UI components

### üë§ User Management
- Create / update / disable users
- Assign / update roles
- Soft delete system
- Invite user by email workflow (API-ready)
- View activity logs for each user

### üß© CRM Modules
- **Leads** (source, stage, assigned manager)
- **Deals** (pipeline, stage management)
- **Notes**
- **Status tracking**
- **Imports/Exports (CSV-ready)**

### üé® UI/UX (EDXcellence Theme)
- Primary Color: `#0B3864`
- Accent: `#00C4CC`
- Light + Dark mode
- Collapsible sidebar
- Responsive layout
- Card-based dashboards
- Clean typography (Inter / DM Sans)
- Glass-UI touches

### ‚öô Backend (NodeJS + Express)
- Modular routing architecture
- Controllers + services separation
- Centralized error handler
- JWT + RBAC middleware
- Mongoose models for user, roles, leads, deals, logs
- Full CRUD APIs
- MongoDB Atlas support

---

## üõ† Tech Stack

### Frontend
- **React (Vite)**
- **Tailwind CSS**
- React Router
- Chart.js
- Context API Auth Layer

### Backend
- **NodeJS**
- **Express**
- **MongoDB + Mongoose**
- JWT Authentication
- RBAC middleware

### DevOps & Deployment
- Frontend ‚Üí **Vercel**
- Backend ‚Üí **Render / Railway**
- Database ‚Üí **MongoDB Atlas**

